sfpsInPortConfigTable.name: sfpsInPortConfigTable
sfpsInPortConfigTable.description: This table contains the configuration information of each configured inbound SFPS switch port. If SFPS is not configured on a port, than an entry will not exist.

sfpsInPortConfigEntry.name: sfpsInPortConfigEntry
sfpsInPortConfigEntry.description: Each entry specifies the SFPS configuration for the SFPS inbound switch port for which the entry exists.

sfpsInPortConfigPort.name: sfpsInPortConfigPort
sfpsInPortConfigPort.description: The primary index to the SFPS in port table. This identifies the inbound SFPS switch port for which the entry exists.

sfpsInPortConfigAdminStatus.name: sfpsInPortConfigAdminStatus
sfpsInPortConfigAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of the SFPS inbound switch port for which the entry exists.

sfpsInPortConfigOperStatus.name: sfpsInPortConfigOperStatus
sfpsInPortConfigOperStatus.description: Indicates the current operating condition of the SFPS on the inbound switch port for which this entry exists.

sfpsInPortConfigOperTime.name: sfpsInPortConfigOperTime
sfpsInPortConfigOperTime.description: Indicates the elapsed time, in hundredths of a second, that sfpsInPortOperStatus has been in its current operational state on the SFPS inbound switch port for which this entry exists.

sfpsInPortConfigType.name: sfpsInPortConfigType
sfpsInPortConfigType.description: Sets the type of port access attribute for the inbound SFPS port for which the entry exists. Access ports allow single user or shared access and perform statisics and control; network ports are equivalent to trunk ports with no access control; host management port indicates the (virtual) port to which the (internal) management agent is attached; host control port indicates the port to redirect non-management packets.

sfpsInPortConfigReservedBW.name: sfpsInPortConfigReservedBW
sfpsInPortConfigReservedBW.description: Sets the amount of Bandwidth that is reserved for the inbound SFPS port for which this entry exists. This bandwidth is set aside for this port and may be given to another port if unused.

sfpsInPortConfigAllocBW.name: sfpsInPortConfigAllocBW
sfpsInPortConfigAllocBW.description: Sets the amount of Bandwidth that is allocated for the inbound SFPS port for which this entry exists. This bandwidth may be less than the reserved bandwidth.

sfpsInPortConfigQoS.name: sfpsInPortConfigQoS
sfpsInPortConfigQoS.description: Sets the desired QoS service class for the inbound SFPS port for which this entry exists.

sfpsInPortConfigQSize.name: sfpsInPortConfigQSize
sfpsInPortConfigQSize.description: Indicates the maximum inbound queue size for this port. Size is indicated in packets (packet descriptors).

sfpsInPortConfigQLen.name: sfpsInPortConfigQLen
sfpsInPortConfigQLen.description: Indicates the actual inbound queue size for this port. Size is indicated in packets (packet descriptors). This is a transient value that reflects the current depth of queue.

sfpsInPortConfigSwitchId.name: sfpsInPortConfigSwitchId
sfpsInPortConfigSwitchId.description: This entry is the id of the port.

sfpsInPortConfigFrontPanelPort.name: sfpsInPortConfigFrontPanelPort

sfpsInPortConfigLinkStateAge.name: sfpsInPortConfigLinkStateAge

sfpsInPortConfigRouterPort.name: sfpsInPortConfigRouterPort
sfpsInPortConfigRouterPort.description: Specifies whether this port is a router port.
